content:
This is great news! Thanks to Administration for Community Living, Americans with disabilities can now call the DIAL hotline to find a COVID-19 vaccine closest to them.

Call 888-677-1199 from 9:00 AM to 8:00 PM ET to connect.

ACL.GOV
HHS Launches Hotline to Improve Access to COVID-19 Vaccines for People with Disabilities | ACL Administration for Community Living

Administration for Community Living
June 8 at 1:26 PM ·

Today, the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services announces the launch of a first-of-its-kind national hotline to connect people with disabilities to information and services to improve access to #COVID19 vaccines.

The Disability Information and Access Line (DIAL) is now available to help people find vaccination locations in their communities, assist with making appointments, and connect callers to local services, like accessible transportation.

Read our full release:
